# Controller Rules - Unusualify Modularity

## Controller Hierarchy

```
CoreController (setup, repository binding)
  ↓
PanelController (auth, caching, scopes, permissions)
  ↓
BaseController (CRUD operations, rendering)
  ↓
YourController (custom logic)
```

## Base Structure

```php
namespace Modules\{ModuleName}\Http\Controllers;

use Unusualify\Modularity\Http\Controllers\BaseController;

class {ModelName}Controller extends BaseController
{
    protected $moduleName = '{ModuleName}';
    protected $routeName = '{routeName}';

    // Index view options
    protected $indexOptions = [
        'create' => true,
        'edit' => true,
        'delete' => true,
    ];

    // Eager loading
    protected $indexWith = ['user', 'category'];
    protected $formWith = ['user', 'category', 'tags'];
    protected $formWithCount = ['comments'];

    // Form configuration
    protected $titleColumnKey = 'name';
    protected $identifierColumnKey = 'id';

    // Permissions
    protected $setDefaultPermissions = true;
}
```

